Hello World for PHP/Zend/MVC framework

Instructions to create this project from scratch:

Project configuration
* install Zend framework (package names maybe zendframework, zendframework-bin)
* configure include_path variable by your chosen method
* "zf create project projectname", execute this command in the location where you want to build your project
* "zf enable layout"
* edit application/controllers/IndexController.php, defining IndexAction function body:
"$this->view->assign('title', 'Hello World');"
*edit application/views/scripts/index/index.phtml to your liking, including these snippet somewhere:
"<title> <?php echo $this->escape($this->title);?> </title>"
"<body> <h1> <?php echo $this->escape($this->title);?> </h1> </body>"

Apache2 configuration
* create virtual host file in /etc/apache2/sites-available
* edit /etc/hosts, adding 127.0.0.1	hellomvc.local
* enable site: a2ensite hellomvc
* reload apache2 config: /etc/init.d/apache2 reload

Point your web browser to hellomvc.local, or whatever entry you put into /etc/hosts

